                           DESCRiPTiON 

 
 The truth about Exercise Tiger, a rehearsal for D-Day on the Devon coast in April 1944 
 that turned into a bloodbath when the US landing craft were ambushed by German E-boats. 
 In the resulting chaos, two of the craft were sunk, leaving an official death toll of 
 749 - but as this documentary shows, that figure may be even higher. Historian Richard 
 Bass uncovers inconsistencies in the documentation and official memorials, talks to UK 
 and US servicemen, and to civilian witnesses - many of whom are speaking about the 
 tragedy for the first time.
